# Parma - Python to SQF Transpiler

Parma is a Python-based framework for [Bohemia Interactive](https://www.bistudio.com/)'s [Armed Assault](http://arma3.com/) version 3. It provides a transpiler for converting Python code to [SQF](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/ArmA:_Introduction_to_Scripting) scripting language, supporting object-oriented programming and modern Python features.

## Features

- **Python to SQF Transpilation**: Write ArmA scripts in Python
- **Object-Oriented Support**: Classes and methods translate to SQF equivalents
- **Modern Python**: Uses Python 3.8+ with type hints and modern tooling
- **Cross-Platform**: Works on Windows, Linux, and macOS
- **CLI Tool**: Easy-to-use command-line interface

## Installation

### From Source

```bash
git clone https://github.com/lotherk/parma.git
cd parma
pip install -e .
```

### Using pip (future)

```bash
pip install parma
```

## Usage

### Basic Compilation

```bash
# Compile a Python file to SQF
parma compile my_script.py

# Specify output file
parma compile my_script.py -o output.sqf

# Verbose output
parma compile my_script.py --verbose
```

### Example

Create a Python script (`mission.py`):

```python
class ArmaMission:
    def __init__(self):
        self.mission_name = "Python Mission"
        self.player_count = 0

    def add_player(self, name):
        self.player_count += 1
        print(f"Player {name} joined")

    def start(self):
        if self.player_count > 0:
            print(f"Mission {self.mission_name} starting!")
        else:
            print("No players to start mission")

# Run the mission
mission = ArmaMission()
mission.add_player("Soldier1")
mission.start()
```

Compile to SQF:

```bash
parma compile mission.py
```

Generated SQF (`mission.py.sqf`):

```sqf
/*
 * Generated by Rarma Python - Python to SQF Transpiler
 */

class ArmaMission {
    def __init__() {
        this.mission_name = "Python Mission";
        this.player_count = 0;
    };

    def add_player(name) {
        this.player_count = this.player_count + 1;
        diag_log format["Player %1 joined", name];
    };

    def start() {
        if (this.player_count > 0) then {
            diag_log format["Mission %1 starting!", this.mission_name];
        } else {
            diag_log "No players to start mission";
        };
    };
};

/*
 * Main execution
 */
_mission = ["new"] call ArmaMission;
["add_player", "Soldier1"] call _mission;
["start"] call _mission;
```

## Project Structure

```
src/parma/
├── __init__.py          # Package initialization
├── cli.py               # Command-line interface
└── transpiler.py        # Core transpilation logic
```

## Development

### Setup

```bash
# Install development dependencies
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# Run tests
pytest

# Run linter
flake8 src/

# Format code
black src/
```

### Building

```bash
# Build package
python -m build

# Install locally
pip install dist/parma-*.whl
```

## Docker Usage

Build and run with Docker:

```bash
# Build the image
docker build -t parma .

# Compile a file
docker run -v $(pwd):/workspace parma compile test_python.py

# Interactive shell
docker run -it -v $(pwd):/workspace parma bash
```

